olor: #ccc;"> is happening today</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">A hearing in the legal battle between Elon Musk and Twitter Inc. is =
scheduled Tuesday afternoon in Delaware Chancery Court for oral arguments o=
ver a range of issues, including Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s request to amend his co=
untersuit.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chancellor Kathaleen McCormick s=
aid in a filing Friday she will consider several pending legal motions from=
 both parties, such as Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s recent request to add allegations=
 from a whistleblower complaint by Twitter=E2=80=99s former head of securit=
y, Peiter Zatko, to his counterclaims.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. =
Musk has also requested that the five-day nonjury trial be pushed to Novemb=
er from October.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The hearing is scheduled t=
o start at 1:30 p.m. ET and each side will be permitted 90 minutes to prese=
nt arguments. The judge said they would begin with the so-called discovery =
motions, over each side=E2=80=99s various requests for information, before =
moving to Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s request to amend his complaint.</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know how this will go. I sup=
pose the main options are:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; paddin=
g-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Chancel=
lor McCormick denies Musk=E2=80=99s request to amend his complaint and the =
trial goes ahead as scheduled, on the fairly narrow issue of whether Twitte=
r was lying about how it counts bot accounts; or</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">She grants Musk=E2=80=99s request to amend his complaint, an=
d probably delays the trial a bit, and Musk gets to <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28964827.283552/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
