></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The second option seems very annoying, a=
nd bad for Twitter. It would mean that Twitter has to defend on lots more f=
ronts. =E2=80=9CMusk is good at muddying waters and impressing the impressi=
onable,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
