there=E2=80=99s more risk of the deal falling apart even if Twitter wins. A=
nd it would <em>perhaps=C2=A0</em>mean that Chancellor McCormick sees somet=
hing in Musk=E2=80=99s claims, that she might believe that he=E2=80=99s ser=
ious when he says that Twitter has been running a comprehensive fraud desig=
ned to trick him into buying it, rather than just being a whimsical rich gu=
y trying to get out of a deal because he overpaid.</p><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">The first option is good for Twitter in some ways: It means that sh=
